    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Nephi",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 6,
        "summary": "Nephi writes of the things of God\u2014Nephi's purpose is to persuade men to come unto the God of Abraham and be saved. About 600\u2013592\u00a0B.C.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And now I, Nephi, do not give the genealogy of my fathers in this part of my record; neither at any time shall I give it after upon these plates which I am writing; for it is given in the record which has been kept by my father; wherefore, I do not write it in this work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 4:15.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:2.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 144
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 163
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 1:17 (16\u201317); 19:1 (1\u20136).",
                        "start": 221,
                        "end": 227
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it sufficeth me to say that we are descendants of Joseph.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 5:16 (14\u201316).",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it mattereth not to me that I am particular to give a full account of all the things of my father, for they cannot be written upon these plates, for I desire the room that I may write of the things of God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 12
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the fulness of mine intent is that I may persuade men to come unto the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, and be saved.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 1:4 (3\u20134); John 20:31 (30\u201331).",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:41 (41, 45, 51).",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, the things which are pleasing unto the world I do not write, but the things which are pleasing unto God and unto those who are not of the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 1:10; 1\u00a0Thes. 2:4; Heb. 13:21; W\u00a0of\u00a0M 1:4.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, I shall give commandment unto my seed, that they shall not occupy these plates with things which are not of worth unto the children of men.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}